rates of planets derived from Kepler, and models for the photometric
performance and sky coverage of the TESS cameras. We expect that TESS
will find approximately 1700 transiting planets from 2\texttimes{}
\{10\}5 pre-selected target stars. This includes 556 planets
smaller than twice the size of Earth, of which 419 are hosted by M dwarf
