brown dwarfs might present differences in period and eccentricity. Conclusions: We find evidence of a non-metallicity dependent
mechanism for the formation of massive brown dwarfs. Our results agree
with a scenario in which massive brown dwarfs are formed as stars. At
high metallicities, the core-accretion mechanism might become efficient
