  abstract = {The false-positive probability (FPP) of Kepler transiting candidates is 
a key value for statistical studies of candidate properties. A previous
investigation of the stellar population in the Kepler field has provided
an estimate for the FPP of less than 5\% for most of the candidates. We
report here the results of our radial velocity observations on a sample
of 46 Kepler candidates with a transit depth greater than 0.4\%, orbital
