explored. We predict that in the primary mission, TESS will discover
about 3500 planets with Neptune size and smaller, half of which will
orbit stars with TESS magnitudes brighter than 12. Specifically, we
proposed a new extended mission scenario that centers Camera 3 on the
ecliptic pole (C3PO), which will yield more long period planets as well
as moderately irradiated planets that orbit F, G, and K stars.},
