considerable difference in collecting area. For ground-based telescopes,
HDC observations can detect an Earth-like planet in the habitable zone
around an M-dwarf star at 10-4 star light suppression
level. Compared to the 10-7 planet/star contrast, HDC
relaxes the star light suppression requirement by a factor of
103. For space-based telescopes, detector noise will be a
major limitation at spectral resolutions higher than 104.
