  abstract = {Context. A first characterization of extrasolar planets by the 
observational determination of the radius has recently been achieved for
a large number of planets. For some planets, a measurement of the
luminosity has also been possible, with many more directly imaged
planets expected in the near future. The statistical characterization of
exoplanets through their mass-radius and mass-luminosity diagram is
