this model for population synthesis calculations. Methods: In
this and a companion paper, we show how we solve the structure equations
describing the gaseous envelope of a protoplanet during the
early-formation phase, the gas runaway accretion phase, and the
evolutionary phase at constant mass on Gyr timescales. We improve the
model further with a new prescription for the disk-limited gas accretion
rate, an internal structure model for the planetary core assuming a
differentiated interior, and the inclusion of radioactive decay as an
additional heat source in the core. Results: We study the in situ
formation and evolution of Jupiter, the mass-radius relationship of
giant planets, the influence of the core mass on the radius, and the
